Today onwards everyone in Melbourne or the Mitchell Shire is required to wear a mask if they leave their home for 1 of only 4 allowable reasons:  1. Shopping for food and essential items. 2. Care and caregiving. 3. Daily exercise. 4. Work and study – if you can’t do it from home.

If you or a family member or friend are unable to wear a mask for medical reasons including mental health, please speak to your GP, psychologist or mental health service provider to be provided with a letter to present to Victoria Police if asked.
If you can't purchase single-use disposable masks, you can use a bandanna, scarf, or make your own mask out of clothing materials following these instructions from DHHS: https://t.co/IrbmzEv6Yp
